 certain\nconditions, first hydrostatic cores can be identified from dust continuum\nemission at 24 microns and 70 microns. We also show that single spectral energy\ndistributions cannot help to distinguish between the formation scenarios of the\nfirst hydrostatic core, i.e., between the magnetized and non-magnetized models.\nSpectral energy distributions are a first useful and direct way to target first\nhydrostatic core candidates but high-resolution interferometry is definitively\nneeded to determine the evolutionary stage of the observed sources.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jul 2012 12:53:10 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 13 Jul 2012 13:40:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
