o, PHL 1092 is a\nquasar with standard X-ray output for its optical luminosity, appearing as\nX-ray weak at times due to absorption; iii) A disc-reflection-dominated\nscenario in which the X-ray emitting corona is confined within a few\ngravitational radii from the black hole at all times. In this case, the\nintrinsic variability of PHL 1092 only needs to be a factor of ~10 rather than\nthe observed factor of ~260.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 3 Jul 2012 14:31:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-05"}
